// @test regression/function-redefinition
// @description Two declarations of the same name with the same arity are illegal unless distinguishable by explicit param type. TV uses three codes: CE10112 (arity 0), CE10113 (same arity, untyped), CE10110 (same arity, same explicit type). A typed-vs-untyped pair, different explicit types, or different arity are legal overloads and stay clean. Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV091.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=5, message=/Function "f" already defined.*number of required parameters in overloaded/
// @expects error: line=9, message=/Function "g" already defined.*without them having distinct types/
// @expects error: line=13, message=/The "h" function has overloads with the same parameters/
// @expects errors: 3

//@version=6
indicator("function-redefinition")
f() =>
    1
f() =>
    2
g(x) =>
    x
g(x) =>
    x + 1
h(int a) =>
    a
h(int b) =>
    b
k(int x) => x
k(string x) => 0
plot(f() + g(1) + h(2) + k(3))
